@NODE Installation "Installation"

@{B}                      - - --÷{· @{BG SHADOW}@{APEN 2}  PSX@{BG HIGHLIGHT}@{APEN 1}Control v1.0  @{BG BACKGROUND} ·}÷-- - -

                         @{B}  ·       @{U}INSTALLATION@{UU}        · @{UB}

   @{B}Hardware installation:@{UB}

   You need a working Net Yaroze cable as hardware. Connect it to the PSX's serial
   port and then connect it to an Amiga Serial port. You might need to purchase
   an adaptor that will convert the 9-pin Yaroze serial connector to a 25-pin
   serial connector.

   For more information on connecting and starting your Net Yaroze, refer to
   your Net Yaroze's starter's guide.

   @{B}Software installation:@{UB}

   The installation is very simple. Copy the PSX-Control executable and icon
   file to a directory of your choice. The documentation can also be put
   anywhere you want it to be.

   For example: Copy everything to a directory called DH0:PSX/

   Before you actually run the program, you might want to have a look at the
   @{"usage" link "Usage"} of PSX-Control.

@ENDNODE

