@NODE Using "Using PSX Control"

@{B}                      - - --÷{· @{BG SHADOW}@{APEN 2}  PSX@{BG HIGHLIGHT}@{APEN 1}Control v1.0  @{BG BACKGROUND} ·}÷-- - -

                         @{B}  ·     @{U}USING PSXCONTROL@{UU}        · @{UB}

   When you start PSXControl, it will open its window (unless you specified
   the @{"CX_POPUP=NO" LINK "Starting"} tooltype). The window looks like
   this:

           @{APEN 2}.---.--------------------------------------------------.---.
           @{APEN 2}|@{APEN 1} · | @{B}PSX Control v1.0@{UB}                                 | · |
           @{APEN 2}|@{APEN 1}---^--------------------------------------------------^---|
      .--- @{APEN 2}|.--------------------------------------------------------@{APEN 1}.|
      |    @{APEN 2}||@{APEN 1}                   .--------.               .--------.  ||
 (1) <     @{APEN 2}||@{APEN 1}  Terminal status: | Online @{APEN 2}|@{APEN 1}  Link Status: | Online @{APEN 2}|@{APEN 1}  ||
      |    @{APEN 2}||@{APEN 1}                   `@{APEN 2}--------'               @{APEN 1}`@{APEN 2}--------'  @{APEN 1}||
      `--- @{APEN 2}|`@{APEN 1}--------------------------------------------------------'|
      .--- @{APEN 2}|@{APEN 1}.--------------------------------------------------------.@{APEN 1}|
 (2) <     @{APEN 2}|@{APEN 1}| PSX Terminal online.                                   @{APEN 2}|@{APEN 1}|
      `--- @{APEN 2}|@{APEN 1}`@{APEN 2}--------------------------------------------------------'@{APEN 1}|
      .--- @{APEN 2}|.------------------.-----------------.-------------------@{APEN 1}.|
      |    @{APEN 2}||@{APEN 1}  Execute Script  | Transfer to PSX | Transfer from PSX ||
      |    @{APEN 2}|`@{APEN 1}------------------^-----------------^-------------------'@{APEN 1}|
 (3) <     @{APEN 2}|.------------------.-----------------.-------------------@{APEN 1}.|
      |    @{APEN 2}||@{APEN 1}       Go!        |                 |                   ||
      `--- @{APEN 2}|`@{APEN 1}------------------^-----------------^-------------------'@{APEN 1}|
           @{APEN 2}`@{APEN 1}----------------------------------------------------------'


   Here you can see :

   @{u}@{b}1) The status of the Net Yaroze@{ub}@{uu}

     The Terminal status is the most important statusreport. It informs you
     if the Yaroze terminal is operational with the current baudrate settings.
     Once the Terminal status is online, you can perform actions (such as
     transfering files, playing music cd's, ...).

     The Link status informs you if the link cable between the Net Yaroze
     and the Amiga is operational with the current device and unit settings.
     Once the Yaroze Terminal has started, this should say "Online". If it
     doesn't then you might want to check your @{" serial settings " LINK "Prefs"}.

     Note: The Terminal status cannot be "Online" when the Link status is
           offline!

   @{u}@{b}2) The status of PSX-Control@{ub}@{uu}

     The status of PSX-Control is shown in the middle of the window. Various
     messages of what is happening internally will be displayed here.

   @{u}@{b}3) Action buttons for PSX-Control@{ub}@{uu}

     These are the gadgets that perform an action when pressed. The following
     gadgets can be pressed:

     @{" Execute Script    " LINK "Scripting"} : This will start the execution of a script.
     @{" Transfer to PSX   " LINK "Transfer2"} : Use this to transfer files to the Net Yaroze.
     @{" Transfer from PSX " LINK "TransferF"} : Press this gadget to read memory from the Net Yaroze.
     @{" Go!               " LINK "StartProg"} : Start the execution of a program.

@ENDNODE

